NAME
	sparkline (display) - render the last column of a history-style file as one anti-aliased trend line with a headline value

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	<mount>		one sample per line: [ts] v1 [v2 ...] — the LAST
			column of each line is the plotted value, oldest
			first.

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	The minimal trend strip: a title (last two path components of
	the mount), the current value as a right-aligned headline, and
	one auto-scaled aadraw polyline with a dot marking the newest
	sample.  No axes, no chrome — compose several in a column for an
	at-a-glance board.  Reads the same "[ts] v1 [v2 ...]" shape as
	line-plot but keeps only the final column, so it works unchanged
	on single-column files and on multi-column rings.  Re-reads the
	file on every update tick and redraws only on change.

SEE ALSO
	line-plot (full axes, every column as a series)
	sysmon-svc, llm-recorder (produce history rings this can graph)
